<p>They could just be a little paranoid given the average life expectancy of retrieval teams around here, but that's a little meta for this one page. As a standalone it does seem odd that they'd pull an armed team out at the first sniff of weirdness—if they were expecting the possibility of losing a whole team so suddenly they'd not send in a bunch of armed men to begin with.</p>
<p>Like Photo said above, it's the way the team's equipment was retrieved that really puts this over the top.</p>

